tions and connections to other work by Falk as well as Levinson and Link, Columbo: Make Me a Perfect Murder sees American television as an intertextual system, from its origins as a commercial broadcast medium to its iterations within contemporary streaming platforms. Ultimately, Hastie argues, in the titular detective’s constant state of learning about cultural trends and media forms, Columbo offers viewers the opportunity to learn with him and, through his tutelage, to become detectives of television itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aColumbo, Lieutenant (Fictitious character). 0aDetective and mystery television programsxHistory and criticism. 0aTelevision broadcastingxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / Genres / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311135689140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478027591?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478027591423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478027591/original  a978-3-11-135689-1  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles